        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 8:18PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 817 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Penderlea, or 9 miles southwest of Wallace, moving southeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Burgaw, Penderlea, White Stocking, Maple Hill, Long Creek, Wards
Corner, Murray Town, Malpass Corner, Willard, St. Helena, Watha, and
Pender Memorial Hospital.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building until the storm passes.</instruction>
